.TH GIT\-ISSUE 1 "2026-03-01" "git-issue 1.0.0-rc1" "Git Issue Tracker"
.SH NAME
git\-issue \- track issues with git notes
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git issue
.I command
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B git\-issue
tracks issues inside a git repository.
Each issue is a git note at
.BI refs/notes/issue\- id
with a 7-character hash ID.
Issues travel with the repo\(empush, pull, clone, and fork all work.
No server required.
.PP
Statuses are configurable.
Edit
.B .git\-issue/statuses
to define your own statuses, colors, and allowed transitions.
.SH COMMANDS
.SS Creating and Viewing
.TP
.BI "create " title " [--description=" desc ]
Create an issue.
Prints the new ID.
.TP
.BI "show " id " [--with-commits]"
Show an issue.
.B \-\-with\-commits
includes linked commits.
.TP
.B list
List all issues, color-coded by status.
.SS Updating
.TP
.BI "update " id " [--status=" s "] [--priority=" p "] [--assignee=" name "] [--description=" desc ]
Change one or more fields.
Flags combine freely.
Status transitions are checked against the status machine (see
.BR "STATUSES" ).
.TP
.BI "comment " "id text"
Add a timestamped comment.
.TP
.BI "link " "id commit"
Link an issue to a commit.
.SS Commit Trailers
.TP
.BI "commit [--issue|--fixes|--closes|--related-to] " id " [--commit " hash ]
Add a trailer to a commit message.
.B \-\-fixes
and
.B \-\-closes
also close the issue.
.B \-\-commit
targets a commit other than HEAD.
.TP
.BI "scan-commits [--since=" date ]
Find issue references in commit trailers.
.SS Import and Export
.TP
.BI "import [--stdin|--file " path "|--bulk " "path ...] [--format=" fmt ]
Import issues.
.B \-\-stdin
reads JSON from standard input;
.B \-\-file
reads one file;
.B \-\-bulk
reads many.
.TP
.BI "export [--format=" fmt "] [" "id ..." ]
Export issues.
Without IDs, exports all.
Format:
.BR github .
.SS Dependencies
.TP
.BI "dep add " "from type to"
Add a dependency.
Types:
.BR blocks ,
.BR depends_on ,
.BR parent_of ,
.BR relates_to .
.RS
.PP
Adding a
.B blocks
edge sets the downstream issue to
.BR blocked .
Closing a blocker unblocks downstream issues that have no remaining blockers.
.RE
.TP
.BI "dep rm " "from type to"
Remove a dependency.
Unblocks the downstream issue if this was its last blocker.
.TP
.BI "dep list [" id ]
List dependency edges, optionally filtered to one issue.
.TP
.B dep rebuild
Rebuild the edge index from scratch.
.SS Queries
.TP
.B ready
List unblocked issues sorted by priority.
Skips issues with an active assignee lease (see
.BR git\-issue (8)).
.\" Future: --full flag to include claimed issues
.TP
.B topo
List non-closed issues in topological (dependency) order.
.TP
.BI "deps [" id "] [--dot]"
Print the dependency graph as text, or as Graphviz DOT with
.BR \-\-dot .
.SS Configuration
.TP
.B statuses
Show configured statuses and transitions.
.TP
.B migrate\-status
Migrate issues from the legacy
.B state:
field to
.BR status: .
Run once after upgrading.
.TP
.BI "setup-sync [enable|disable|status]"
Toggle automatic git notes sync on push and pull.
.SH STATUSES
Six statuses ship by default:
.BR open ,
.BR in_progress ,
.BR review ,
.BR blocked ,
.BR deferred ,
.BR closed .
.PP
To customize, edit
.BR .git\-issue/statuses .
Each line defines a status or transition:
.PP
.RS
.nf
mode: permissive
status: open     | default | Not yet started
status: closed   | gray    | Done
transition: open \(-> closed
.fi
.RE
.PP
In
.B strict
mode, invalid transitions are rejected.
In
.B permissive
mode (the default), they produce a warning.
.PP
Changes take effect on the next
.B git issue
invocation.
.SH PRIORITIES
.BR low ,
.BR medium
(default),
.BR high ,
.BR critical .
.SH DEPENDENCIES
.TS
l l l.
Type	Meaning	Blocks ready?
_
blocks	X must close before Y starts	Yes
depends_on	Inverse of blocks	Yes
parent_of	Epic/subtask grouping	Yes
relates_to	Soft link	No
.TE
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
# Create an issue
git issue create 'Fix login timeout' \-\-description='Sessions expire too early'

# Work on it
git issue update a1b2c3d \-\-status=in_progress \-\-priority=high

# Add a dependency
git issue dep add a1b2c3d blocks b2c3d4e

# Find ready work
git issue ready

# Close via commit trailer
git issue commit \-\-fixes a1b2c3d

# Import from GitHub
gh issue list \-\-json number,title,body,state,author,createdAt,updatedAt,url \e
  | gh\-to\-git\-issue | git issue import

# Dependency diagram
git issue deps \-\-dot | dot \-Tpng \-o deps.png

# Claim work (agent)
git issue update a1b2c3d \-\-status=in_progress \-\-assignee='agent\-3'

# Show status machine
git issue statuses
.fi
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B GIT_DIR
If set, locates the git repository.
Outside a repo,
.B git\-issue
uses an XDG-compliant standalone directory.
.SH FILES
.TP
.B .git\-issue/statuses
Status definitions. Track this in git.
.TP
.B .git\-issue/statuses.bash
Compiled statuses. Auto-generated; add to
.BR .gitignore .
